                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/symfony/edit/master/knpu/extra-form-theming/form-theme-validation-icon.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>Checkout Bootstrap's form documentation. Under validation, they have a cool feature:
when your field has an error, you can add a cute icon. I want a cute icon! To get
it, we just need to add a <code>has-feedback</code> class to the div around the entire field
<em>and</em> add the icon itself.</p>
<p>Right now, each field is surrounded by a div with a <code>form-group</code> class. How can we
<em>also</em> add a <code>has-feedback</code> class to this? Answer: override the block that's responsible
for rendering the <em>row</em> part of every field. In other words, the <code>form_row</code> block.</p>
<p>In <code>form_div_layout.html.twig</code>, search for the <code>form_row</code> block. There it is!</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="e87953d499">
